ðŸŽ¯ What is Optional?

A container object that may or may not hold a non-null value.
Introduced in Java 8 to avoid NullPointerException and promote functional programming.

- Optional.of(value)	
  Wraps non-null value (throws if null)
- Optional.ofNullable(value)
  Wraps value (null allowed)
- Optional.empty()
  Creates an empty Optional

There are other methods as well.